  "wiringNotes": [
    "I-02 (_IO_EM_DI_02) is NC wired — healthy state is TRUE; open = E-stop tripped",
    "I-03 (_IO_EM_DI_03) is NO wired — healthy state is FALSE; closed = E-stop tripped",
    "Wiring fault condition: both DI_02 and DI_03 in same state (XOR expected for healthy wiring)",
    "O-02 (_IO_EM_DO_02) drives safety contactor Q1 — energizes only when e-stop healthy and no wiring fault",
    "Direction selector is 2-wire: DI_00=FWD, DI_01=REV — both active simultaneously triggers dir_fault",
    "DI_05/DI_06 are sensor inputs — DI_06 used as SensorEnd for item counting on rising edge",
    "VFD command words: 1=STOP, 18=FWD+RUN, 20=REV+RUN (GS10 proprietary register 0x2000)",
    "Modbus server v3 (plc/MbSrvConf_v3.xml) is authoritative — v2 in plc/ccw/controller is an older snapshot",
    "Ignition writes vfd_cmd_word and vfd_freq_setpoint via Modbus HR:115 and HR:116",
    "Ignition MCP at 100.72.2.99:8765 was OFFLINE at manifest generation time — tag paths unconfirmed"
  ],
